- id: 3586-better-javascript-prompting
  title: Better JavaScript Prompting
  tags:
  - web-development
  - better
  - javascript
  - prompting
  family: Web Development
  body: Hi ChatGPT, I will send you some javascript code or ask you to create it.
    Use 'let' for variables or 'const'. Write the complete code in only one block.
    Use proper variable, parameters and etc names for [TARGETLANGUAGE], but keep the
    name of the functions that I indicate. Use only single quotes in the code. When
    using increment operator, use "i += 1" instead of "i++". And write "I'm done writing"
    at the end of each message in the specified language. All the text message should
    be written in [TARGETLANGUAGE]. [PROMPT]
  enabled: true
  required:
  - prompt
  - targetlanguage
